  "market_context": "EUR/USD 5-minute chart on Fri 27 Jun '25. After a prior bearish move, an hourly candle closes bullish forming a reversal (consolidation, expansion out, expansion back in). Price then begins building a new bullish leg with structure shifting upward.",
  "key_observation": "Once a protected swing forms and the trend reverses bullish, a shallow retracement into a fair value gap followed by a closure over the down-close candles offers a clean continuation long entry, with nearby failure-swing highs as targets.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify the protected swing — note that if violated, the prior trend is over, and observe a fair value gap forming as a retracement zone.",
    "Step 2: Recognize the retracement stalls into consolidation (failure to close below), warning that this is no longer a clean retracement but a consolidation on the lows.",
    "Step 3: Confirm reversal via the hourly candle closing bullish (consolidation, expansion out, expansion back in pattern).",
    "Step 4: Reset bias bullish and look for continuation signatures — ideally a sweep of consolidation lows to provide a trustworthy wick to long from.",
    "Step 5: Note that equal lows form instead of a clean sweep, so skip the first long opportunity and wait for price to trade higher and offer a continuation setup.",
    "Step 6: Observe expansion higher followed by a shallow retracement into a fair value gap; wait for a closure over the down-close candle rather than longing immediately.",
    "Step 7: Take entry on the close (or retest) with stop on the wick (or slightly above the body), targeting at least 2R toward the failure swing highs left on the chart."
  ],
  "outcome": "Entry was triggered on the closure over the down-close candle; TP outcome unknown as it was current price action at the time of analysis.",
  "lessons": "Not every setup will be perfect — sometimes the initial sweep or fair value gap retracement is missing. Patience to wait for the next valid continuation signature (FVG + closure over opposing candles at a protected swing) preserves participation in the move.",
